This paper is primarily focused on vehicular networks and communication, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of interference and the need for balancing awareness and interference, which could fall under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a model for calculating neighborhood awareness, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of simulations to explore achievable performance, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) if the simulations involve visualizations or other multimedia elements.
